President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Bruce A. Heyman as Ambassador to Canada, Kathryn Thomson as General Counsel for the Department of Transportation, and Kevin Whitaker as Ambassador to the Republic of Colombia. He also announced his intent to appoint Jim Powell as the Representative of the United States to the Southern States Energy Board. Heyman is currently the Managing Director of Private Wealth Management at Goldman Sachs & Co. Thomson has been serving as Acting General Counsel at the Department of Transportation and Chief Counsel of the Federal Aviation Administration. Whitaker is the Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for South America and has previously served in various positions at the Department of State. Powell is the owner and Principal Consultant at Norava Consulting and has previously served in roles at the U.S. Department of Energy and the U.S. Department of the Navy.